{"expireTime":9007200839544227000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-ast-9f221f2e475eac75ce310968333ea851-gatsby-plugin-sharpgatsby-remark-imagesgatsby-remark-responsive-iframegatsby-remark-prismjsgatsby-remark-copy-linked-filesgatsby-remark-smartypantsgatsby-remark-emojis-","val":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"This had been a crazy week! Juggling work (internship) at Phaidon Press and attending several job interviews (including one for an arts organisation which I am particularly excited about), I thought it´s time have some respite from this intense week. I did the best I could and have explained why I am the best person for the job and it´s really all up to the heavens now. Longing for something zen to bring back balance in my life, I visited ","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":444,"offset":444},"indent":[]}},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"link","title":"Fred Sandback","url":"http://fredsandbackarchive.org/","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Fred Sandback","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":447,"offset":447},"end":{"line":2,"column":460,"offset":460},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":446,"offset":446},"end":{"line":2,"column":510,"offset":510},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":"´s","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":510,"offset":510},"end":{"line":2,"column":512,"offset":512},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":444,"offset":444},"end":{"line":2,"column":514,"offset":514},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" retrospective at the ","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":514,"offset":514},"end":{"line":2,"column":536,"offset":536},"indent":[]}},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"WhiteChapel","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":538,"offset":538},"end":{"line":2,"column":549,"offset":549},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":536,"offset":536},"end":{"line":2,"column":551,"offset":551},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" gallery. The artist, who died in 2003, is known internationally for his concept-based minimalist sculptures using the barest and simplest materials like acrylic yarn.","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":551,"offset":551},"end":{"line":2,"column":718,"offset":718},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":718,"offset":718},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Unlike his contemporaries such as Carl Andre, ","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":720},"end":{"line":4,"column":47,"offset":766},"indent":[]}},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Sandback has been overlooked throughout the years","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":49,"offset":768},"end":{"line":4,"column":98,"offset":817},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":47,"offset":766},"end":{"line":4,"column":100,"offset":819},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" but this retrospective shows that Sandback was as great as all the other Minimalist artists of his time. Sandback had been fascinated with stringed instruments when he was young hence the interest with strings and wires as material for his geometrical pieces.","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":100,"offset":819},"end":{"line":4,"column":360,"offset":1079},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":720},"end":{"line":4,"column":360,"offset":1079},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"His artworks are crafted to achieve volume without mass resulting in sculptures that are drawn directly from the air","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":3,"offset":1083},"end":{"line":6,"column":119,"offset":1199},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1,"offset":1081},"end":{"line":6,"column":121,"offset":1201},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":" – using the architecture of the room, ceiling, floor etc as geometrical points. ”The first sculpture I made with a piece of string and a little wire was the outline of a rectangular solid … lying on the floor. It was a casual act, but it seemed to open up a lot of possibilities for me,” Fred Sandback wrote in 1986.","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":121,"offset":1201},"end":{"line":6,"column":442,"offset":1522},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1,"offset":1081},"end":{"line":6,"column":442,"offset":1522},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"html","title":"Untitled (Sculptural Study Seven Part Triangular Construction)","url":"./images/5943060772_821f10f164_z.jpg","alt":null,"position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1,"offset":1524},"end":{"line":8,"column":107,"offset":1630},"indent":[]},"value":"\n  <figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n  \n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/190b335995f9ec967cc7288e8bd22ec4/c08c5/5943060772_821f10f164_z.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 640px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"5943060772 821f10f164 z\"\n        title=\"Untitled (Sculptural Study Seven Part Triangular Construction)\"\n        src=\"/static/190b335995f9ec967cc7288e8bd22ec4/c08c5/5943060772_821f10f164_z.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/190b335995f9ec967cc7288e8bd22ec4/e07e9/5943060772_821f10f164_z.jpg 200w,\n/static/190b335995f9ec967cc7288e8bd22ec4/066f9/5943060772_821f10f164_z.jpg 400w,\n/static/190b335995f9ec967cc7288e8bd22ec4/c08c5/5943060772_821f10f164_z.jpg 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n  <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Untitled (Sculptural Study Seven Part Triangular Construction)</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n      "}],"position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1,"offset":1524},"end":{"line":8,"column":107,"offset":1630},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"I was particularly drawn to ","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1,"offset":1632},"end":{"line":10,"column":29,"offset":1660},"indent":[]}},{"type":"strong","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Untitled (Sculptural Study Seven-Part Triangular Construction)","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":31,"offset":1662},"end":{"line":10,"column":93,"offset":1724},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":29,"offset":1660},"end":{"line":10,"column":95,"offset":1726},"indent":[]}},{"type":"text","value":". The biggest piece in the retrospective, Untitled draws seven triangular spaces from black yarn whose bases are pinned to the floor with points reaching up to the ceiling. I took several turns to observe the space that it occupied, each step as contemplative and meditative as I discovered prisms criss-crossing in pedestrian space, a term which he himself has coined to explain how his work is much a part of the environment that envelops it. For me, Fred Sandback is truly great artist because his pieces allow the viewer to contemplate and imagine form while going thru an actual experience of interacting with the work much like Richard Serra.","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":95,"offset":1726},"end":{"line":10,"column":743,"offset":2374},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1,"offset":1632},"end":{"line":10,"column":743,"offset":237